<P>N. B. With a view to render this Publication more u&s;eful and intere&s;ting than any other of a &s;imilar nature, it is propo&s;ed to &s;elect the articles it &s;hall contain, as well from the Analytical and Critical, as from the Monthly Reviews, publi&s;hed in England. The Editor will there|by be enabled to pre&s;ent his readers with <HI>more u&s;eful,</HI> and <HI>le&s;s u&s;ele&s;s</HI> critici&s;m, &s;hould his &s;election be judicious, than is to be found in either of the&s;e Reviews: With the Monthly Review, therefore, as his general guide, he &s;hall occa&s;ionally extract valuable articles from the other critical performances, and give a ready in&s;ertion to &s;uch original, productions as may be entitled by their merit to impartial approbation. The Editor earne&s;tly invites the learned and ingenious of his fellow-citizens to enrich with their labours, and make more worthy of American patronage, this u&s;eful publication.</P>
